<subSubSection id="61ADDBE97449BF5DCBA3F93EFB0DFA51" pageId="1" pageNumber="56" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="290888627449BF5DCBA3F93EFB0DFA51" blockId="1.[151,1436,1387,1523]" pageId="1" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis id="1BC354707449BF5DCBA3F93EFEBBFA26" bold="true" box="[151,266,1387,1412]" pageId="1" pageNumber="56">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="EEB7F3E17449BF5DCA2BF93EFECDFA21" authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1820" box="[287,380,1387,1411]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Phthiria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1BC354707449BF5DCA2BF93EFECDFA21" box="[287,380,1387,1411]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="56">Phthiria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only representative of the subfamily 
<taxonomicName id="EEB7F3E17449BF5DC8A9F93EFBA9FA26" authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1913" box="[925,1048,1387,1412]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Phthiriinae">Phthiriinae</taxonomicName>
in the Palaearctic Region. This subfamily is closely related to the 
<taxonomicName id="EEB7F3E17449BF5DC92CF9DAFDDCFA0A" box="[536,621,1423,1448]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Usiinae">Usiinae</taxonomicName>
but easily separated from it by an apical sulcus bearing a style, presence of dorsal and/or ventral processes on first flagellomere, presence of M2 cell on the wing (four posterior cells) and absence of lateral papillae on the sperm pump (
<bibRefCitation id="4D26F5937449BF5DC99CF98FFCEAFA51" author="Evenhuis" box="[680,859,1498,1523]" pageId="1" pageNumber="56" refString="Evenhuis, N. L. (1990) Systematics and evolution of the genera of the subfamilies Usiinae and Phthiriinae of the world (Diptera: Bombyliidae). Entomonograph, 11 (1989), 1 - 72." type="journal article" year="1990">Evenhuis, 1990</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="4D26F5937449BF5DC852F98FFB01FA51" author="Greathead" box="[870,1200,1498,1523]" pageId="1" pageNumber="56" refString="Greathead, D. J. &amp; Evenhuis, N. L. (2001) Bombylioidea (Diptera: Bombyliidae; Mythicomyiidae) from the island of Socotra. Zootaxa, 14 (1), 1 - 11." type="journal article" year="2001">Greathead &amp; Evenhuis, 2001</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
